div2.p:
Mr. Grew sat speechless a moment, staring blankly at his son; 
then he emitted a puzzled laugh.  "My money?  What are you talking 
about?  What's this about my money?  Why, it ain't  mine, Ronny; 
it's all yours—every cent of it!" he cried.

Ronald's walk had once more brought him beneath the photograph 
on the wall.  He lifted his head for a moment and looked at it; 
then he looked again at Mr. Grew.
